<item>
            <title>[FELIX-4014] handleAspectAwareRemoved in ServiceDependencyImpl can cause a possible deadlock</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-4014</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;the handleAspectAwareRemoved invokes a callback method within a synchronization block. Since we don&apos;t know what will be going there this can cause (and in our case does cause) concurrency issues.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix would be to move the invoke out of the sync block.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
